## Step 9: Completing the square in $x$ and $y$ terms, we have
\begin{align*}
x^2 - 80x + y^2 - 100y &= (x^2 - 80x + 400) + (y^2 - 100y + 1000) - 400 - 1000 \\
&= (x - 20)^2 + (y - 50)^2 + 600.
\end{align*}

## Step 20: Since $u = x + \frac{1}{2}y$ and $v = x - \frac{1}{2}y$, we can write
\begin{align*}
u+v &= x + \frac{1}{2}y + x - \frac{1}{2}y \\
&= 2x.
\end{align*}
